fg_segments: Privacy Policy Last Modified: June 14, 2012 Thank you for visiting GrammarBook.com.
We are committed to respecting your privacy and security as a visitor to this website (the "Site").
This Privacy Policy is intended to help you understand the policies of the Site related to online privacy and customer security.
If you have any questions or comments about this Privacy Policy, please feel free to contact us at ###**...
JavaScript must be ENABLED to view Jane's e-mail address...**###.

Types of Information Collected Information Provided By You This Site collects personal information online, including names, postal and e-mail addresses, and billing information, entered by the visitor in order to join our mailing list or register with the Site.
Information Collected and Stored Automatically This Site is not set up to track, collect, or distribute personal information not entered by visitors.

However, as with many websites, the Site logs do generate certain kinds of non-personally identifiable information, such as your Internet Protocol (IP) address and the time of your visit, as well as site usage data (e.g., the number of hits and visits to the site).
Information Collected By Third Party Advertisers The Site uses Google, a third party vendor, to host customized advertisements that may be of interest to you, the visitor.
Google uses cookies to serve ads on the Site.
Specifically, Google uses the DART cookie to serve ads to our visitors based on your visit to the Site and other sites on the Internet.
When you view an ad, or click on an ad supported by Google's advertising services, Google may set a cookie on your browser.
The use of cookies is fairly standard on many websites.
Most browsers are initially set up to accept cookies.
Should you desire, you can change your browser's settings to either refuse to accept cookies or notify you when they are placed on your computer.
You can also opt out of the use of the DART cookie by visiting the Google ad and content network privacy policy.
How Information Is Used Information Provided By You The Site will use your personal information only for the purpose for which it is submitted.
If you have difficulty removing yourself from our database, you can contact us directly at ###**...
JavaScript must be ENABLED to view Jane's e-mail address...**###.
Information Collected and Stored Automatically This information is used for internal purposes only.
The statistics generated by the site do not contain personally identifiable information and cannot be used to gather such information.
Information Collected By Third Party Advertisers We use a third-party, Google, to serve ads when you visit the Site.

Google may use information (not including your name, address, e-mail address, or telephone number) about your visits to this and other websites in order to provide advertisements about goods and services of interest to you.
If you would like more information about this practice and to know your choices about not having this information used by these companies, click here.
We partner with ValueClick to serve ads and/or collect certain information when you visit our website.

ValueClick may use cookies or web beacons to collect non-personally identifiable information during your visit to this website in order to help show advertisements on other websites likely to be more interesting to you.
To learn more about this "behavioral advertising" practice or to opt-out of this use of your anonymous information, you can click here.
Protection of Information GrammarBook.com has employed physical, electronic, and managerial procedures to safeguard the security and integrity of personal information.
GrammarBook.com encrypts credit card information. Release of Information The Site will never rent or sell your personal information.
We may, however, release personal information without your consent pursuant to a court order or as required by law.

How to Correct or Remove Your Information If you would like to correct or update any information you have provided to GrammarBook.com, or if you would like to remove your information from our database, please contact us at ###**...
JavaScript must be ENABLED to view Jane's e-mail address...**###. Links to Third Party
Sites This Privacy Policy concerns only the Site and does not concern any website to which the Site may link.

Should you choose to visit these third-party sites, you should review their privacy policies to ensure that you understand and are comfortable with their practices concerning your personal information.
Privacy Policy Changes This Privacy Policy may be revised or supplemented from time to time.
We anticipate that such changes will be minor. We will post any Privacy Policy changes on this page, and should the changes be significant, seek to provide a more prominent notice.
If you are concerned about how your information is used, you should check back at our Site periodically.
Compliance If you have a complaint about GrammarBook.com's compliance with this privacy policy, please contact us at ###**...JavaScript must be ENABLED to view Jane's e-mail address...**###.

Privacy Policy 
Last Modified: June 14, 2012 
Thank you for visiting GrammarBook.com. We  are committed to respecting your privacy and security as a visitor to this  website (the “Site”). This Privacy Policy is intended to help you  understand the policies of the Site related to online privacy and customer  security. 
If you have any questions or comments about this Privacy Policy,  please feel free to contact us at  ###**...JavaScript must be ENABLED to view Jane's e-mail address...**###. 
Types of Information Collected 
Information Provided By You 
This Site collects personal information online, including names,  postal and e-mail addresses, and billing information, entered by the visitor in  order to join our mailing list or register with the Site.  
Information Collected and Stored Automatically 
This Site is not set up to track, collect, or distribute personal  information not entered by visitors. However, as with many websites, the  Site logs do generate certain kinds of non-personally identifiable information,  such as your Internet Protocol (IP) address and the time of your visit, as  well as site usage data (e.g., the number of hits and visits to the site). 
Information Collected By Third Party Advertisers 
The Site uses Google, a third party vendor, to host customized  advertisements that may be of interest to you, the visitor. 
Google  uses cookies to serve ads on the Site. Specifically, Google uses the DART  cookie to serve ads to our visitors based on your visit to the Site  and other sites on the Internet.  When you view an  ad, or click on an ad supported by Google’s advertising services, Google may  set a cookie on your browser. 
The use of cookies is fairly standard on many  websites. Most browsers are initially set up to accept cookies. Should you  desire, you can change your browser's settings to either refuse to accept  cookies or notify you when they are placed on your computer. You can also opt out of the use  of the DART cookie by visiting the Google ad and  content network privacy policy.
How Information Is Used 
Information Provided By You 
The Site will use your personal information only for the purpose  for which it is submitted.   If you have difficulty removing yourself  from our database, you can contact us directly at  ###**...JavaScript must be ENABLED to view Jane's e-mail address...**###. 
Information Collected and Stored Automatically 
This information is used for internal purposes only. The  statistics generated by the site do not contain personally identifiable information  and cannot be used to gather such information. 
Information Collected By Third Party Advertisers 
We use a third-party, Google, to serve ads when you visit the  Site. Google may use information (not including your name, address, e-mail  address, or telephone number) about your visits to this and other websites in  order to provide advertisements about goods and services of interest to  you. If you would like more information about this practice and to know  your choices about not having this information used by these companies, click here.
We partner with ValueClick to serve ads and/or collect  certain information when you visit our website. ValueClick may use cookies or  web beacons to collect non-personally identifiable information during your  visit to this website in order to help show advertisements on other websites  likely to be more interesting to you. To learn more about this “behavioral  advertising” practice or to opt-out of this use of your anonymous information,  you can click here.
Protection of Information 
GrammarBook.com has employed physical,  electronic, and managerial procedures to safeguard the security and integrity  of personal information. GrammarBook.com encrypts credit card  information. 
Release of Information 
The Site will never rent or sell your personal information. We  may, however, release personal information without your consent pursuant to a  court order or as required by law.
How to Correct or Remove Your Information 
If you would like to correct or update  any information you have provided to GrammarBook.com, or if you would like to remove your information  from our database, please contact us at  ###**...JavaScript must be ENABLED to view Jane's e-mail address...**###.  
Links to Third Party Sites 
This Privacy Policy concerns only the Site and does not concern  any website to which the Site may link. Should you choose to visit these  third-party sites, you should review their privacy policies to ensure that you  understand and are comfortable with their practices concerning your personal  information. 
Privacy Policy Changes 
This Privacy Policy may be revised or supplemented from time to  time. We anticipate that such changes will be minor. We will post any  Privacy Policy changes on this page, and should the changes be significant,  seek to provide a more prominent notice.  If you are concerned about how  your information is used, you should check back at our Site periodically.
